@{b}Green:@{ub}

    This gadget determines whether the green component of the colour palette should be cycled. If it is not checked, then the green component of the colour palette will stay exactly as it is.
    For the other gadgets pertaining to green to accept keyboard shortcuts it must be active. Green is active if there is a raised box around the green gadgets. Green is inactive if there is a recessed box around the green gadgets.
    To make green active, use the @{b}R@{ub} shortcut. Green does not need to be active for this specific gadget to function, but it does need to be active for the shortcuts for the @{" Green Waveform Type " link Gad_GreenWave }, @{" Green Phase Slider " link Gad_GreenPhaseSlider }, @{" Green Speed Slider " link Gad_GreenLenSlider }, @{" Green Mean Slider " link Gad_GreenMeanSlider } and @{" Green Amplitude Slider " link Gad_GreenAmpSlider } gadgets to work.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}g@{ub}.
    The keyboard shortcut to activate Green is @{b}G@{ub}.
@endnode

