@{b}Green Amplitude Slider:@{ub}

    This slider will allow you to change the green amplitude.
    This gadget has a range of 0 to 255. It has a default value of 128.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}a@{ub} to increase the value.
    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}A@{ub} to decrease the value.
@endnode

@node Gad_Blue "ColourCycle Gadgets"
@{b}Blue:@{ub}

    This gadget determines whether the blue component of the colour palette should be cycled. If it is not checked, then the blue component of the colour palette will stay exactly as it is.
    For the other gadgets pertaining to blue to accept keyboard shortcuts it must be active. Blue is active if there is a raised box around the blue gadgets. Blue is inactive if there is a recessed box around the blue gadgets.
    To make blue active, use the @{b}R@{ub} shortcut. Blue does not need to be active for this specific gadget to function, but it does need to be active for the shortcuts for the @{" Blue Waveform Type " link Gad_BlueWave }, @{" Blue Phase Slider " link Gad_BluePhaseSlider }, @{" Blue Speed Slider " link Gad_BlueLenSlider }, @{" Blue Mean Slider " link Gad_BlueMeanSlider } and @{" Blue Amplitude Slider " link Gad_BlueAmpSlider } gadgets to work.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}b@{ub}.
    The keyboard shortcut to activate Blue is @{b}B@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Gad_BlueWave "ColourCycle Gadgets"
@{b}Blue Waveform Type:@{ub}

    This gadget specifies the waveform type for blue. The available options are "Off", "Sine", "Triangular", "Ramp Up" and "Ramp Down". See @{" Theory " link Theory } for more information.
    A value of "Off" will cycle the existing colour palette. Other values will mean that a new palette for blue will be algorithmically generated.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}w@{ub} to go forward through the cycle gadget's choices.
    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}W@{ub} to go backward through the cycle gadget's choices.
