@node Menu_Project "ColourCycle Project Menu"
@{b}Project Menu:@{ub}

    This menu gives general control over the whole project.

@{b}Menu Items:@{ub}

    @{" New        " link Menu_Project_New }
    @{" Open...    " link Menu_Project_Open }

    @{" Save       " link Menu_Project_Save }
    @{" Save As... " link Menu_Project_SaveAs }

    @{" About...   " link Menu_Project_About }

    @{" Quit       " link Menu_Project_Quit }
@endnode

@node Menu_Project_New "ColourCycle Project Menu"
@{b}New:@{ub}

    Select this menu option to close the current project (if one is open), and start with a fresh new workspace. It gives reasonable defaults to start with. You can then select the menu item @{" Project Open... " link Menu_Project_Open } to start working on an existing project.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}Right Amiga-n@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Menu_Project_Open "ColourCycle Project Menu"
@{b}Open...:@{ub}
    Select this menu option to close the current project (if one is open), and start work on an existing project.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}Right Amiga-o@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Menu_Project_Save "ColourCycle Project Menu"
@{b}Save:@{ub}

    Select this menu item to save the current project. If this is a new unnamed project, a file requester will pop up for you to enter in a file name. If this is an already existing project it will silently update that file.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}Right Amiga-s@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Menu_Project_SaveAs "ColourCycle Project Menu"
@{b}Save As...:@{ub}

    Select this menu item to save the current project. Regardless of whether this is a new unnamed project or an existing project, a file requester will pop up for you to enter in a file name. If a file with the name you supply already exists, @{b}ColourCycle@{ub} will be ask you whether you wish to overwrite that file before it does. You can cancel this if you do not wish to overwrite that existing file.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}Right Amiga-a@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Menu_Project_About "ColourCycle Project Menu"
@{b}About...:@{ub}

    Selecting this menu option will provide you with some information about @{b}ColourCycle@{ub}.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}Right Amiga-?@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Menu_Project_Quit "ColourCycle Project Menu"
@{b}Quit:@{ub}

    This menu item will quit @{b}ColourCycle@{b}. If you have a project that you have changed since it was last saved, you will be prompted as to whether you wish to @{" Save " link Menu_Project_Save } the project before you quit.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}Right Amiga-q@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Menu_Settings "ColourCycle Settings Menu"
@{b}Settings Menu:@{ub}

    This menu gives general control over the whole application settings.

@{b}Menu Items:@{ub}

    @{" Create Icons? " link Menu_Settings_CreateIcons }

    @{" Save Settings " link Menu_Settings_SaveSettings }
@endnode

@node Menu_Settings_CreateIcons "ColourCycle Settings Menu"
@{b}Create Icons?:@{ub}

    This item toggles on and off. When in the checked (on) state, all projects will be saved with icons.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}Right Amiga-i@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Menu_Settings_SaveSettings "ColourCycle Settings Menu"
@{b}Save Settings:@{ub}

    This item will save the following settings:
    -   Current position of the main window.
    -   Current public screen the window is open on.
    -   The state of the @{" Create Icons? " link Menu_Settings_CreateIcons } menu item.
    -   The state of the @{" Advanced " link Gad_Advanced } gadget/@{" Advanced Window " link AdvWindow }.
    -   The current or last position of the @{" Advanced Window " link AdvWindow }.

    When @{b}ColourCycle@{ub} is started up next, the window(s) will try to be opened on the saved public screen at the saved position(s). If the public screen cannot be found at startup, then it will revert back to the Workbench screen.

    This item has no keyboard shortcut.
@endnode

@node Menu_Help "ColourCycle Help Menu"
@{b}Help Menu:@{ub}

    This menu gives access to the on line help.

@{b}Menu Items:@{ub}

    @{" Contents... " link Menu_Help_Contents }
    @{" Gadgets...  " link Menu_Help_Gadgets }
    @{" Menus...    " link Menu_Help_Menus }
    @{" Index...    " link Menu_Help_Index }
@endnode

@node Menu_Help_Contents "ColourCycle Help Menu"
@{b}Contents...:@{ub}

    This menu item will open up the on line help window (if it is not already open), and show the contents page.

    The keyboard shortcut is @{b}Right Amiga-h@{ub}.
@endnode

@node Menu_Help_Gadgets "ColourCycle Help Menu"
@{b}Gadgets...:@{ub}

    This menu item will open up the on line help window (if it is not already open), and show a list of gadgets relating to the current window.

    This item has no keyboard shortcut.
@endnode

@node Menu_Help_Menus "ColourCycle Help Menu"
@{b}Menus...:@{ub}

    This menu item will open up the on line help window (if it is not already open), and show a list of menus.

    This item has no keyboard shortcut.
@endnode

@node Menu_Help_Index "ColourCycle Help Menu"
@{b}Index...:@{ub}

    This menu item will open up the on line help window (if it is not already open), and show the index.

    This item has no keyboard shortcut.
@endnode

@node SysGads "ColourCycle System Window Gadgets"
@{b}System Window Gadgets:@{ub}

    @{" Close Gadget  " link SysGads_Close }
    @{" Drag Bar      " link SysGads_Drag }
    @{" Zoom Gadget   " link SysGads_Zoom }
    @{" Depth Gadget  " link SysGads_Depth }
    @{" Resize Gadget " link SysGads_Size }
@endnode

@node SysGads_Close "ColourCycle System Window Gadgets"
@{b}Close Gadget:@{ub}

    This will quit the current project. If it has been changed since it was last saved, you will be asked whether you wish to save it before it closes it.

    Being a system gadget, it has no keyboard shortcut.
@endnode

@node SysGads_Drag "ColourCycle System Window Gadgets"
@{b}Drag Bar:@{ub}

    Use this to move the window to a new place. To use it, hold down the left mouse button while you move the mouse. Let the left mouse button go when you have it at the desired position, or press the right mouse button while still holding the left to cancel the window move.
@endnode

@node SysGads_Zoom "ColourCycle System Window Gadgets"
@{b}Zoom Gadget:@{ub}

    This button lets the user have two preset sizes and positions for the window. Pressing this button toggles between the two settings. By resizing or moving the window, the current setting is changed.

    Being a system gadget, it has no keyboard shortcut. However, you may be able to assign this functionality to a keyboard shortcut by using the standard system Commodity program called @{b}FKey@{ub}. Consult either the @{b}Using The System Software@{ub}, @{b}Workbench 3.0@{ub} or @{b}Workbench 3.1@{ub} manual supplied with your machine or operating system upgrade.
@endnode

@node SysGads_Depth "ColourCycle System Window Gadgets"
@{b}Depth Gadget:@{ub}

    Use this to bring this window to the front. If it is already at the front, then it will be placed behind all other windows.

    Being a system gadget, it has no keyboard shortcut. However, you may be able to assign this functionality to a keyboard shortcut by using the standard system Commodity program called @{b}FKey@{ub}. Consult either the @{b}Using The System Software@{ub}, @{b}Workbench 3.0@{ub} or @{b}Workbench 3.1@{ub} manual supplied with your machine or operating system upgrade.
@endnode

@node SysGads_Size "ColourCycle System Window Gadgets"
@{b}Resize Gadget:@{ub}

    Use this to change the size of the window. To use it, hold down the left mouse button while you move the mouse. Let the left mouse button go when you have it at the desired size, or press the right mouse button while still holding the left to cancel the window resize.

    Being a system gadget, it has no keyboard shortcut. However, you may be able to assign this functionality to a keyboard shortcut by using the standard system Commodity program called @{b}FKey@{ub}. Consult either the @{b}Using The System Software@{ub}, @{b}Workbench 3.0@{ub} or @{b}Workbench 3.1@{ub} manual supplied with your machine or operating system upgrade.
@endnode

